item.content:
&lt;h1&gt;Conger Shortcode feature examples&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Wrap existing field name with shortcode tag inside page content and get this tag replaced with found field value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;[$field_name$]&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unique or same shortcodes can be included as many times as needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Shortcode result of site_email field&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[$site_email$]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Shortcode result of unknown1 field&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[$unknown1$]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Shortcode result of cpath field&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[$cpath$]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Shortcode result of another_unknown field&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;[$another_unknown$]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Shortcode results for cpath, site_email and missing fields.&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conger client path is &#039;[$cpath$]&#039;, site email is [$site_email$].&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If shortcode has unknown field, that shortcode renders as initial: [$missing$]&lt;/p&gt;
